  <li id="comment-10561" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/07/hot-and-sweet/#comment-10561"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-07-09T19:06:00-04:00">Wednesday, July 9, 2008 at 7:06 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This seems to be a version of goi xoai xanh, Vietnamese green mango salad or the similar Thai dish yum mar mour. People allergic to mangoes (and there are quite a few allergic to the skin of mangoes as the toxin is related to poison ivy) might want to make the papaya version, som tom, the Thai salad traditionally made with green papaya, fish sauce, chilis, dried shrimp, coriander leaf, etc.</p>
    </div>

